Lightly coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray. Heat over medium heat. Cook ground turkey in hot skillet about 5 minutes or until no longer pink. Drain off any fat. Stir in beans (if desired), corn, salsa, and water. Bring to boiling; reduce heat. Simmer, covered, for 2 to 3 minutes to blend flavors. Line 4 salad bowls or plates with lettuce. Top with hot turkey mixture. Sprinkle with cheese. Serve immediately.